{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ed571d14-3976-4645-83fe-856a87d5a473","content":"The issue is the **F# file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. F# requires files to be listed in dependency order — a file can only reference types/modules from files listed *before* it.\n\nCurrently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`. Fixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_017BQ8YWdYLZL8qCxSw8wcQR","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-ed6a5518f129497bb262bd28b104c4f3/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-ed6a5518f129497bb262bd28b104c4f3/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"bb04a38a-8c99-4eda-8560-b0db80aa1843","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters. Files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nIn the `.fsproj`, the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` \n2. `Domain.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), so `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs`. Also, `Program.fs` depends on both, so it should be last.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs`\n\n\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":426,"requestId":"781A:2BFBA0:80F31:A1BD4:69F549FB"},"id":"f435a33c-8f0e-4ec3-b694-a7b0f0d9a41f","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:49:08.990Z","parentId":"c62633a6-1d8b-4c4f-b984-122f09bc4a8d"}
